    "updated_at": "2016-04-26T14:22:36Z",
    "body": "Got same bug today, when had try to send response over express(string is converted to buffer inside res.send). Error occurs, when you try to get Buffer from string with more that 4096 length.\n\nTemporary fix you can use in your project is next one:\n\nvar encoder = new TextEncoder()\nres.send(new Buffer(encoder.encode(LONG_LONG_STRING))); \n\nThis could get array of characters codes to your buffer instead of string directly. \n\nAlso it's seems to be electron-specific bug, node doesn't crash on it.\n"
